== Names of Countries in Wikipedia ==

If the name of an article is a name (a sequence of cmevla), then periods are needed nor in front, nor after each cmevla. But in the text of the article they are needed as in any other Lojban text.

So, if the article is about {la .antiguas.}, then it should have the address {antiguas}. [[User:Inego|Inego]] 02:51, 20 August 2006 (UTC)

:would you like to give a rational for that? i initially thought that way, but i now notice that, for example, an article about <.iecuax. pe la natsyrat.> would be called such, but without the tail it would just be <.iecuax> with the former scheme, which seems inconsistent.  mi'e [[User:Bobas|bobas]] 03:23, 20 August 2006 (UTC)

::If the name of the article ''isn't'' of form {la + sequence of cmevla}, then it is written in the full form: {la glico selmikce}, or, in your case, {la .iecuax. pe la nazaRET}. If we omit {la} here, the resulting *{.iecuax. pe la nazaret.} will be ''ungrammatical''. At the same time, the final and starting periods are never needed in names of Wikipedian articles, -- for the sake of not increasing the enthropy. [[User:Inego|Inego]] 14:39, 20 August 2006 (UTC)

